race.comment: COSSACK WARRIOR (3) hit the frame two starts back at Canberra when a narrow second. Total forgive from the wide barrier when raced without cover for a fading last over 1425m at Moruya. Nicely placed to turn things around from the inside barrier. No excuses today. CLIMATE CHANGE (2) sprinted quickly at her first run back when a decisive winner over 1000m at Albury. Second-up form is just as strong and she looms as a significant threat. CASHBOOK (1) up in grade and trip when a fading ninth over 1400m at Canberra in C2 class. Blinkers come off and assess on the good win two-back at Gundagai. NIGHTS INFERNO (6) improved performance when he chipped away late to run sixth over 1200m at Goulburn. Expect to see him take a hand in the finish.
